n_class = 3
y_train_cat = tf.keras.utils.to_categorical(y_train, num_classes=n_class, dtype="int32")
y_test_cat = tf.keras.utils.to_categorical(y_test, num_classes=n_class, dtype="int32")

In [20]:
p = n_input
normalizer  = tf.keras.layers.experimental.preprocessing.Normalization(input_shape=[p,])
normalizer.adapt(X_train_tensor)
In [21]:
model = tf.keras.Sequential([
    normalizer,
    tf.keras.Input(shape=(p,)),
    tf.keras.layers.Dense(p*6, activation='relu'),
    tf.keras.layers.Dense(p*4, activation='relu'),
    tf.keras.layers.Dense(p*2, activation='relu'),
    tf.keras.layers.Dense(n_class, activation='softmax')
])

model.compile(optimizer=tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(),
              loss=tf.keras.losses.CategoricalCrossentropy(),
              metrics=['accuracy'])
